values: The wrongly-titled photoalbum is gone (don't lie and say you called it a scrapbook, you didn't), as well as any other memento that may have been kept. Pasts can be undone so long as both of us have forgotten, and let's face it, I was always the one with the better memory. If no one is there to remember it, did it really happen? 'Ruining me' is a little harsh, isn't it? No need now I'm sure, but did you really think that I ever wanted you back? Don't you think I would have said something myself if I had? I pity myself for how naive I was but more so, I pity others who have known you longer and still don't know you. A little hypocritical to call me the liar, and if I had lied, whose 'truth' if farther from the reality? Forgiveness isn't likely had the whole truth come out, like you committed murders and got caught for a petty theft. You are a lucky guy but you don't deserve the luck you've had. Goodbye
